Connector catalog reference data (community tier)
-------------------------------------------------
The connector catalog MAY include community-tier reference rows derived from
server/provider metadata published by two upstream catalogs:

    MCP Registry — https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry   (PRIMARY)
    Copyright (c) the Model Context Protocol authors and contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

    open-connector — https://github.com/oomol-lab/open-connector       (SUPPLEMENT)
    Copyright (c) oomol-lab and contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

These rows are imported as UNTRUSTED reference data by the offline tool in
crates/fluidbox-catalog-import (see
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-14-connector-catalog-bulk-import.md). Each such
row records its origin in its `provenance` column
({"source":"mcp-registry"|"open-connector","source_ref":"<pinned cursor/commit>",
"upstream_id":"...", ...}), and the generated migration header records the exact
upstream snapshot/commit it was produced from. No upstream source code is
vendored, executed, or linked; only factual metadata (names, descriptions,
categories, remote URLs, auth types, and scopes) is redistributed, with
attribution, per the Apache-2.0 license.

The default checked-in catalog ships only fluidbox-curated (verified) rows;
an import migration is merged separately and is gated on the attribution/legal
review noted in the plan (D8 / open question O1).
